@startuml 27-core-law-sequence
title Core Law Sequence — UInstruction Moves, Data Stays Resident

skinparam shadowing false

participant "Data Plane\nUniverseBlock U_t\n[u64; 4096]" as DP
participant "UniverseScratch\nPlane S\noperands + masks" as SP
participant "Admission Kernel\n(branchless mask algebra)" as AK
participant "UReceipt\nR_t (rolling hash)" as RCPT
participant "UProjection\n(disposable view)" as PROJ

SP -> AK : bring tiny UInstruction\n(instruction_id, scope, input_mask, output_mask)

AK -> DP : test lawful motion:\n(U_t & input_mask) == input_mask

note right of AK
  Instructions move to the universe.
  The universe does NOT move to instructions.
  T0 ≤ 2ns — single branchless word op.
end note

AK -> DP : transition scoped words (branchless):\nnext = select(enabled, (U & !I) | O, U)

DP -> SP : emit UDelta:\nΔU = U_t ⊕ U_{t+1}\n(only changed words, sparse)

DP -> RCPT : update UReceipt:\nR_{t+1} = mix(R_t, instruction_id, ΔU)

DP -> PROJ : update projections from UDelta:\nView_i = π_i(U_t)

note right of PROJ
  UProjection is NOT authority.
  Authority is ΔU + UReceipt.
  Projections are disposable —
  regenerate from receipt + replay.
end note

@enduml
